== Description ==
Connect to a setup node (or all nodes) by cluster id on eLab

== Requirements ==

sudo easy_install pexpect

== Usage ==

    = External script =
    Usage: essh.sh [-v] [-C] <CID> [ss2env.py args]
    Where:
        -C - Clear Cached json
        -v - Verbose
    Examples:
        # Connect to emanage 0 on setup 208
        essh.sh 208 -e0
        # Open a session to each node in setup 208
        essh.sh 208 -Aa
        # Add your public key (only needed once/setup) to all nodes and open a session to each node in setup 208
        essh.sh 208 -Aa
        # Clear cached json and connect to loader 5 on setup 208
        essh.sh -C 30 -l5



    = Internal script =
    usage: ssh2env.py [-h] (-l LOADERS | -e [EMANAGE] | -v | -a) [-u USER_NAME]
                      [-p PASSWORD] [-k PUBLIC_KEY] [-A]
                      conf_file

    Connect to a test setup node specified by type [and id]

    positional arguments:
      conf_file             JSON configuration file

    optional arguments:
      -h, --help            show this help message and exit
      -l LOADERS, --loader LOADERS
                            Loader id
      -e [EMANAGE], --emanage [EMANAGE]
                            eManage id
      -v, --vip             eManage VIP
      -a, --all             Connect to all nodes
      -u USER_NAME, --user USER_NAME
                            User name
      -p PASSWORD, --password PASSWORD
                            User password
      -k PUBLIC_KEY, --public_key PUBLIC_KEY
                            Public key file
      -A, --add_key         Add keys to vHeads

